Business Brief -- Amtech Corp.:
   Stock Offering Is Planned
   Totaling 2.2 Million Shares
Amtech said it plans to use the proceeds for working
capital, research and development, increased marketing,
capital expenditures to expand manufacturing capacity and
other general purposes.
   Amtech said that 400,000 shares would be sold by American
President Cos. and 225,000 would be sold by Mitsubishi Corp.,
Amtech's Asian distributor. Amtech said that both companies
will retain substantial stakes in Amtech after the offering.
   Alex. Brown  Sons Inc. is leading the underwriting group.